items.name: Mastering-AI-02---Python-Libraries-Frameworks-for-AI
items.description: Welcome to the `Mastering AI 02 - Python Libraries/Frameworks for AI` repository! This repository aims to provide a detailed and structured overview of essential Python libraries and frameworks for AI, including data handling, machine learning, deep learning, and more.

items.name: Machine-Learning-Framework
items.description: A custom machine learning framework similar to pytorch. Created for learning purposes.

items.name: payments-fraud-model
items.description: A machine learning-powered fraud detection framework to enhance transaction security for payment gateways, reducing fraud incidents by 35%.

items.name: DeepMol
items.description: DeepMol: A Machine and Deep Learning Framework for Computational Chemistry

items.name: IncomePredictor-Predicting-Economic-Disparities-Using-ML
items.description: This project follows the CRISP-DM framework with the objective of developing a machine learning model that predicts whether an individual, based on specific characteristics, is likely to earn above or below a $50,000 threshold. The models will then be deployed for practical use.

items.name: Mainh_on
items.description: Machine Learning Framework for Everyone

items.name: Evidencia2MachineLearning_A01753898
items.description: Evidencia 2 del mdulo de aprendizaje mquina. Consiste en hacer uso de un modelo de machine learning utilizando un Framework, en este caso: Scikit-Learn en Python.

items.name: formacaoMachineLearningSpecialist
items.description: Neste repositrio so apresentadas tcnicas avanadas  exibindo o potencial ilimitado de algoritmos de Machine Learning, envolvendo modelos de Deep Learning e outras tcnicas do estado-da-arte, tcnicas de aprendizado supervisionado e no supervisionado, modelos implementados em Python e R, os principais frameworks e bibliotecas.

items.name: 2024-cms-EnhancedActiveLearning
items.description: Source code for all machine learning algorithms and enhanced active learning frameworks included in the manuscript

items.name: TrialTranslator-notebooks
items.description: A collection of Jupyter Notebooks demonstrating data cleaning, machine learning model development, and trial emulation for the TrialTranslator framework.

items.name: Streamlit_CFDM_app
items.description: This project was built as machine learning project [Type: Classification]. The original dataset is the Credit Card Fraud Detection dataset on kaggle (https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mlg-ulb/creditcardfraud), there were no missing values and less preprocessing was done.  The model was deployed using Streamlit an opensource framework for data science and machine learning webapps. Check it out: https://share.streamlit.io/kinematic2002/streamlit_cfdm_app/main/main_streamlit.py

items.name: stocks-ai
items.description: This code was created using Django framework and machine learning modules in python. It receives a stock symbol, start date and end date as inputs and delivers 3 predictions for the next day, using 3 different machine learning caluclations -

items.name: Women-Safety-and-Analytics
items.description: The Real-Time Surveillance and Analytical Solution is designed to enhance public safety, with a particular focus on protecting women from potential threats. The system integrates advanced video analytics, machine learning, and real-time monitoring to create a proactive and responsive safety framework.

items.name: ACON
items.description: A dynamic and adaptive machine learning framework designed for maximum optimization and adaptability across diverse datasets and environments. This is an open-source project, so please, feel free to share improvements/comments/suggestions

items.name: MachineLearningImageRecognation
items.description: In this project, you will learn how to integrate CoreML into a Swift application. CoreML is a framework that enables the use of machine learning models in Apple platforms. We utilize the MobileNetV2 model for image classification. Additionally, this project highlights the differences between DispatchQueue.main.async and DispatchQueue.global.

items.name: MLonBAO
items.description: Framework for Impact Analysis of Contention on Multi-Core Platforms for Real-Time Critical Applications and Machine Learning

items.name: Planter
items.description: Planter is a modular framework for realising in one-click in-network machine learning algorithms.

items.name: Interactive-ML-Model-Deployment-with-GUI
items.description: This project focuses on embedding machine learning models into an interactive, user-friendly application using Streamlit, enabling third-party stakeholders to make real-time predictions without technical knowledge. The project follows the final step of the CRISP-DM frameworkdeployment, ensuring the model is accessible for practical decision-making

items.name: UNVEILING-THE-LUNG-CANCER-ENIGMA-A-MULTI-AGENT-SYSTEMS-ML-FOR-PRECISION-PREDICTION-AND-ANALYSIS
items.description: Unraveling the complexities of lung cancer through a groundbreaking multi-agent systems framework. Our project leverages machine learning for precision prediction and analysis, offering a novel approach to combat this deadly disease.

items.name: porter
items.description: porter is a framework for exposing machine learning models via REST APIs.

items.name: Flower-AWS-FederatedLearning
items.description: An implementation of federated learning using the Flower framework on AWS. It enables distributed machine learning across multiple devices while preserving data privacy. The system leverages AWS services for scalable and secure deployment.
